Character

Kenneth Kozlow first appears in The Pitiful Human-Lizard #1 and fights alongside Lucas Barrett who is The Human Lizard. He is the self-proclaimed king of Toronto Underworld and uses an army of trained rats and alligators.

Powers & Abilities

Kozlow has the power to control animals and named them after baseball players from the 1992-93 World Series Champions.

deck: Dimwit is a Terrytoons cartoon character who is enemy with Heckle and Jeckle.
description: Dimwit is a Terrytoons cartoon character who is enemy with Heckle and Jeckle. He first appeared in The Talking Magpies, along with Heckle and Jeckle, as the pet of Farmer Al Falfa. Then, Dimwit appeared in more Heckle and Jeckle shorts like: Uninvited Pests, McDougal's Rest Farm, Happy Go Lucky, Fishing By The Sea, The Super Salesman, The Hitch Hikers, Out Again, In Again, Free Enterprise, The Stowaways, Hula Hula Land, The Fox Hunt, Merry Chase, Bargain Daze, Mint Men, and Trapeeze, Pleeze. After these cartoons, Jim Tyer decided to make his own short-lived series from that first was How To Keep Cool. Dimwit seems to have a goofy personality and most of the situations will be familiar to anybody who has seen Jack Kinney's excellent Goofy cartoons from the early 50s.
name: Dimwit

Origin

Frostbite has been a top secret U.S. government funded project since 1951. In 1993 project Frostbite was complete.

deck: Photon Leader of Terra Corp.  Has the power over Atoms.
description:
The three identical brothers had acquired a piece of land that they wanted to start building a new plant. The construction team discovered a crashed spacecraft. As the three brothers began exploring the outside of the craft its hyperspace engines engaged and it was sucked into hyperspace. The three brothers were caught on the edge of it and they merged into one being. Photon was born. Photon had all the intelligence of all 3 brothers. The three brothers were experts in each of the fields (Engineering, Robotics, and Biology).

He immediately took control of the company and renamed the corporation Terra Corp and started making great strides in robotics and artificial limbs. After the Great Invasion the company became the number one privately owned researcher for alien technology. They have illegally gained access to several Alien artifacts.

Photon, wishes to protect the world but he can only do that if he rules it. He thinks in terms of numbers. Photon doesn't care if thousands of people must die to save a million. Mathematically its worth it in the end.

Photon Powers

Photon has the ability to control inorganic molecules. The bioenergy created by living entities disrupts photons ability to effect living beings. Although he can still effect them indirectly by creating energy blast and force fields. Thanks to his unique brain. Photon can created artificial limbs out of nothing. They can be surgically attached to anyone. To date he has reconstructed whole bodies except the brain.

Photon can effect his own molecules. This has allowed him to become far more durable and his strength has increased beyond any normal human. This also allows him to heal any wounds almost instantly.

Photon can also make worm holes. These worm holes can transport himself or someone any where in the sol system. He can also force someone to come to him if he knows their exact location.

issue_credits.name: Force Lotus Mandrake vs The World

name: Photon

volume_credits.name: Global Defense Force: Lotus Mandrake vs The World

deck: Part of Terra Corp. The first cyborg Photon made and is completely loyal to Photon.
description:
Sgt Grimes fought during Afghanistan Tour for the US Army. His company was completely overrun by insurgents he was the only survivor. When he awoke in the hospital he found out he had no arms or legs. He went into a depression. Photon found out about Sgt Grimes and offered him a chance to add purpose to his life again. Tank had 85% of his body replaced with cybernetics.

He is now Photon's muscle. He has no problems killing people to get an assignment done. This is not known if its due to his military upbringing or some cybernetic enhancement that Photon installed.

Tank Powers

Tank possesses cybernetic enhancements that provide superhuman strength, speed, endurance, and durability. Tank can also interface with computers.

His boots allow him to fly at subsonic speeds. He can communicate with Terra Corps satellites and have instant communications with Photon, if needed. He has built in infrared and sound enhancers.

He carries a two specialized gun in his legs. These guns can be reconfigured while they are in his legs to suit whatever need that Grimes might want. The guns he has produced so far are Assault Rifles, grenade launchers, flame throwers, and sniper rifles.

He also wears a telepathy resistant helmet. This helmet has been known to mask his thoughts to people with telepathy. It reduces any mental powers that effect Tanks mind.

issue_credits.name: Force Lotus Mandrake vs The World

name: Tank

volume_credits.name: Global Defense Force: Lotus Mandrake vs The World

deck: The last member to join Terra Corp. Is in charge of Security and has a hatred for Manchine.
description:
Roger was a police officer for Las Vegas Police department. He liked helping people for the most part. During the Great Invasion his family was caught in the middle of it. While trying to save his family from being absorbed. The @Tree of Life was teleported by @Manchine into space. Rogers arms which were touching the vines were also teleported.

By the time Electric Marshal woke up the war was over. He had lost his arms. It was all Manchines fault. His wife had left him taking his kids to live with another man. This was all Manchines fault. Photon found Roger and offered him a new life. At first he refused but Photon made mention that he would be contacting Manchine in the near future and that was all Roger needed to hear. Photon installed a cybernetic arms and gave him power armor. Roger soon became known as Electric Marshal and was head of Photons Security.

Electric Marshals Powers

Electric Marshal possesses cybernetic arms that increases his strength beyond normal human standards. This allows him to lift about 10 Tons.

He can fly by magnetically charging any metal and flying on it. This allows him to fly at subsonic speeds. He can communicate with Terra Corps satellites and have instant communications with Photon, if needed.

He has an internal air supply and can survive in outer space for a limited time. Sensors consisted of radar, sonar, infrared scanners, and radio.

issue_credits.name: Force Lotus Mandrake vs The World

name: Electric Marshall

volume_credits.name: Global Defense Force: Lotus Mandrake vs The World

deck: A mercenary for hire that likes to use guns. Is a permanent member of Terra Corp.
description:
James had been working as a mercenary for years now. His military background with sniper training made him the perfect sniper. He had done some big gigs. The shooter that was never found when King Vertimal was killed was him. Ambassador Rhyekyl from the Ukraine was shot in his car driving on open roads through tinted bullet proof glass. This was a feat few people could pull off. Marksmen had heard of a company looking for special individuals. He was able to contact Photon by phone and specifically told Photon he wanted someone like him. Photon hung up. A second later a bullet hit dead center on Photons computer screen. A call came in again and Photon was impressed and took Marksmen as one of his personal attendant's.

Marksmen Powers

Marksmen eye has been replaced special optic that allows him even greater accuracy. He is a master of stealth and even before is optic upgrade he is one of the most accurate snipers in the world.

His specialized gun has a number of add-ons that he can adjust before he leaves to go any a mission. Marksmen is always the one that is ready for a fight. Marksmen will run away without hesitation if he is not prepared for something.

With Photon's backing Marksmen always has high tech traps in areas when he expects things to happen. He carries a few items with him that have saved him several times. One of which is a Monofilament dagger that can cut through just about anything on a molecular level.

issue_credits.name: Force Lotus Mandrake vs The World

name: Marksman

volume_credits.name: Global Defense Force: Lotus Mandrake vs The World

deck: Wanting more thrills Power Claw joined Terra Corp.
description:
Photon wanted an expert hand to hand fighter. He looked into the army and found Roxanne. She was in jail for almost killing her senior drill instructor. Roxanne knew she was one of the best fighters around but she was always held back by rules. When Photon approached her in jail she just thought about how this could get her out. After seeing what Photon could give her. She decided to stick around. She was pretty much free to hurt people and she liked it. She also liked the little toys she could use. The first time Photon sent her loose she killed all the targets and half her own squad.

Power Claw Powers

When Power Claw gets into combat she loses all semblance of right and wrong. Wounds don't phase her. Thanks to some an injection of nanites wounds heal very fast on her. These same nanites fuel her berserker rage helping her to become a killing machine.

Power Claw wears two large Gauntlets. She forms claws out of these gauntlets. Her strength is greatly increased from the gauntlets. She can even fire ninja stars out of her gauntlets.

She considers herself the best fighter in the world. No doubt she is one of the best but time will only tell if she is as good as she thinks.

name: Power Claw

volume_credits.name: Global Defense Force: Lotus Mandrake vs The World

deck: Captain of Science
description:
Origin

Jet Powers was an athlete and engineering genius who from his base in a carved out mesa in the West flew out to confront a number of menaces from space threatening the Earth.

At first working alone he is later joined in his mission by former villainess Su Shan.

Together they deal with space war lords, alien swarms of intelligent insects, evil inventors with earthquake machines, or rays that turn paper into useless white powder, natural disasters from outer space, and a disreputable disgraced general who tries to turn America into a dictatorship under his control.

Creators

Jet Powers was created by Bill Powers and Gardner Fox and ran for four issues in A-1 Comics, Magazine Enterprise‚Äôs tryout comic, but did not prove popular enough to gain a regular series.

The series is of note for having one of the first interracial couples in comics, also instead of being a series of disconnected stories the adventures of Jet and Su refer to past adventures, so that in one story a renegade disgraced general is able to create a fascist dictatorship in America because of the havoc caused by an unrelated disaster from outer space that took place in a pervious issue.
name: Jet Powers
